[b][color=#ff0000]Nordzy-Cursors theme[/color][/b] 

Cursor theme using the [url=https://github.com/arcticicestudio/nord] Nord [/url] color palette, based on [url=https://github.com/vinceliuice/Vimix-cursors] Vimix [/url] and [url=https://github.com/charakterziffer/cursor-toolbox]cz-Viator [/url].

[b]
#################
#### Installation  ####
#################
[/b]
[b]Installer[/b]
To use the installer, go to the GitHub[url=https://github.com/alvatip/Nordzy-cursors] page [/url] and follow the instructions.

[b]tar.gz files[/b]
Alternatively, you can use the tar.gz files and extract them to the adequate directory.
For local installation:
[code]
tar -zxvf Nordzy-cursors.tar.gz -C $HOME/.icons/
tar -zxvf Nordzy-cursors-white.tar.gz -C $HOME/.icons/
[/code]
For system-wide installation: 
[code]
tar -zxvf Nordzy-cursors.tar.gz -C /usr/share/icons/
tar -zxvf Nordzy-cursors-white.tar.gz -C /usr/share/icons/
[/code]
[b]Set the cursor theme[/b]

There are various way to set this (or another) cursor theme.
You will find all the needed information on this [url=https://wiki.archlinux.org/title/Cursor_themes#GNOME]ArchWiki[/url] page.

[b]Uninstall[/b]
If you installed it locally, run this command in your terminal: 
[code]
rm -r $HOME/.icons/Nordzy-cursors*
[/code]
And if you installed it system-wide use:
[code]
sudo rm -r /usr/share/icons/Nordzy-cursors*
[/code]
